President Obama has declared a major disaster in Tennessee and authorized federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts following severe storms, tornadoes, and flooding that occurred from February 28 to March 1, 2011. The federal funding will be provided on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, facility repairs, and replacements in various counties affected by the disaster. Additionally, funding will be available for statewide hazard mitigation measures. W. Montague Winfield has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and based on damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.